---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Base title="DigiPets — Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for the DigiPets mobile app.">
  <Header currentPath="/privacy/digipets" />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[1280px] px-12 pt-36 pb-20 max-md:px-6 max-md:pt-20">
    <div data-i18n="pp_label" class="mb-7 text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[2.5px] text-accent">
      Privacy Policy
    </div>
    <h1 data-i18n="pp_title" class="mb-6 max-w-[620px] text-[42px] font-light leading-tight tracking-tight max-md:text-3xl">
      DigiPets
    </h1>
    <p data-i18n="pp_effective" class="mb-12 text-sm text-text-3">Effective date: July 12, 2026</p>

    <div class="max-w-[600px] space-y-10">
      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_intro" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Introduction</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_intro" class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          DigiPets ("the App") is a free virtual pet game developed by David Luky ("we", "us"). This policy explains what data the App collects, how it is used, and your rights.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_collect" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">What we collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          <li data-i18n="pp_c1">An anonymous user ID generated by Firebase Authentication. No email or legal name is required to use the App.</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_c2">Game progress data (pet stats, inventory, coins, achievements) stored in Cloud Firestore and associated with your anonymous ID.</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_c3">If you choose to link an email/password account, that email is stored securely by Firebase Authentication.</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_c4">If you use Friends, social data such as your shareable friend code, active pet name and summary, friendships, requests, visits, house summary, and kudos activity.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_not_collect" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">What we do not collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          <li data-i18n="pp_nc1">Location data</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_nc2">Contacts or phone number</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_nc3">Photos, camera, or microphone access</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_nc4">Device identifiers or advertising IDs</li>
          <li data-i18n="pp_nc5">Third-party analytics, advertising tracking, or crash-reporting SDKs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_use" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">How we use your data</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_use" class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          We use your data to save game progress, support optional account linking, and provide Friends, requests, and visits. We do not sell or monetize your data. Limited social profile details are shown through friend-code and accepted-friend flows; friend, request, and visit records are scoped to the involved accounts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_thirdparty" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Third-party services</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_tp" data-i18n-html class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          The App uses <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" class="border-b border-accent/30 text-accent no-underline transition-colors hover:border-accent">Google Firebase</a> for authentication, cloud data storage, and server-side game and social commands. Firebase's own privacy policy applies to data processed by its infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_children" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_children" class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          The App is not directed to children under 13 and does not knowingly collect their personal information. Anonymous play does not require an email or legal name. If you believe a child has provided personal information, contact us and we will delete it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_deletion" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Data deletion</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_deletion" data-i18n-html class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          You can request deletion of all your data at any time by emailing <a href="mailto:davidluky@davidluky.com" class="border-b border-accent/30 text-accent no-underline transition-colors hover:border-accent">davidluky@davidluky.com</a>. We will delete your account and all associated game data within 30 days.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_changes" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_changes" class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 data-i18n="pp_h_contact" class="mb-3 text-[13px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text">Contact</h2>
        <p data-i18n="pp_contact" data-i18n-html class="text-[15px] leading-[1.85] text-text-2">
          Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:davidluky@davidluky.com" class="border-b border-accent/30 text-accent no-underline transition-colors hover:border-accent">davidluky@davidluky.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<script>
